  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  between 18 and 80

          -  ASA I or II

          -  with symptomatic gallstone disease which requires elective laparoscopic
             cholecystectomy

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  acute cholecystitis, cholangitis, severe acute pancreatitis, advanced liver cirrhosis
             or suspected gallbladder cancer,

          -  a medical history of epilepsy, cardiac arrhythmias or chronic pain of any kind, -
             allergy to amid type drugs

          -  pregnancy

          -  patients suffering from hypotension or hypovolemia

          -  infectious liver disease

          -  conditions obstructing adequate pain scoring

          -  patients using drugs that deduce function of the CYP3A4 or CYP1A2 system

          -  patients having an American Society of Anaesthesiologists (ASA) classification of
             three or higher.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
